#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:208
#: scenarios/2_Beginning_of_the_Crusade.cfg:218 scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:186
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:1081
msgid "Uuugh..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:222
msgid "Arrgh... We lost!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:236
msgid "Seems I underestimated the enemy..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:244
msgid ""
"Arr, that was a long way! Look, Barkuk, the smoke is above our villages!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Castellan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:248
msgid ""
"By the Light, the noble Pan Shrogg has arrived to help us! The enemy has "
"been pillaging our villages, but we with serfs are defending the castle. Now "
"the enemies are preparing an assault!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:252
msgid ""
"Enemies amassed a great force to storm the castle. The serfs won't stand for "
"long, we must come swift and strike invaders hard."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=enemy1
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:256
msgid "Forward, brothers! The ogres will pay for attacking our allies!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:273
msgid "With divine help, we won!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:277
msgid ""
"This victory came at a high price. Castellan, how did such a formidable army "
"end up under the walls of my castle?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Castellan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:281
msgid ""
"They came here out of the blue on the sixth week since your departure, noble "
"pan. I immediately sent messengers to you and to the neighbors, but no one "
"answered. ThenI gathered the serfs and began defending the castle. Without "
"you, we'd have no chance to win in open combat."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:285
msgid ""
"Although we managed to hold the castle, our lands are devastated, we have "
"lost many knights and mercenaries. How are we supposed to get back to "
"Lintanir now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:289
msgid ""
"Not this year, Barkuk. Winter is coming. Even if our villages were intact, "
"and our army fully intact, we would not make it before the first snows. We "
"don't need to add soldiers dying from frost and hunger to the problems we "
"already have."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:293
msgid ""
"Exactly! I'm sure the cowardly elves set this up! Having us attacked in "
"autumn so we can't return to their forests for months..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:297
msgid ""
"Uh-huh. Seems the rumors about them forming an alliance with Krad were true."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:301
msgid "Ugh, so, what now? The crusade is over for us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:305
msgid ""
"If you don't want to stand in the shadow of other pans and pick up their "
"leftovers, then yes. During this year, the king will seize and divide the "
"best lands, even if we return, we'll get nothing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:309
msgid "What do we do now then?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:313
msgid ""
"Hmm... We killed the lion's share of the Krad's troops. This means that the "
"knyaz is now as open to attack as we were."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:317
msgid "But a lot of warriors died too."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:321
msgid ""
"We will easily gather more mercenaries and knechts no worse than the ones we "
"lost. And the knyaz will not replenish the army so quickly. There are few "
"seekers of gold and battles in his domain. Here's what: we will restore the "
"villages before winter. You will gather more warriors, I will go to the Ogre "
"Pope, so that he will bless our cause. We will move out in the spring, at "
"the same time as the steppe ogres, so that Krada's forces can be divided. "
"Thus begins our own crusade."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:325
msgid "Our own crusade, you say?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:329
msgid ""
"Yes. We will turn the northerners to the light with fire and sword, make "
"their lands our possessions and surpass all the pans in glory!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:333
msgid "Quite an grand plan you have come up with, brother, I like it!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/1_Smoke_of_the_Fatherland.cfg:337
msgid ""
"Ho-ho! May the Light witness this, brother - in six months the most glorious "
"deed in the history of our family will begin!"
msgstr ""

