#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:595
msgid "Finally, we reached Shumsk."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:607
msgid "The city indeed looks well-fortified: sturdy walls, plenty of towers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:611
msgid "Good that our siege equipment made it without any trouble."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=engineer1
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:623
msgid ""
"At your service, sir! Remember, as we agreed, the payment will be 28 gold "
"per catapult and 22 gold per battering ram."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=engineer2
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:636
msgid "Time to turn the enemy walls into rubble, hehe."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:641
msgid ""
"To build siege weapons, use the rightclick menu on a tile next to your "
"engineer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:646
msgid "Time to see which of us will kill the city's commander first."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:651
msgid "A competition, eh? I like that idea. Let's go!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:710
msgid "You are their kinsmen, why aren't you fighting us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:714
msgid ""
"Kinsmen!? You couldn't find a worse insult, ogre! We don't want to have "
"anything in common with these cowardly Krad weaklings, who forgot the true "
"ancestry, the forefathers. You are attacking them, aren't you? I'll gladly "
"help you, provided that you pay me 95 gold."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:725
msgid "I can't afford your services right now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:729
msgid ""
"Come back when you loot some gold then. We'll be staying at this camp in the "
"meantime."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:736
msgid "Hmmmm... should I hire them?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:739
msgid "Yes (costs 95 gold)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:765
msgid ""
"(to his men) Alright lads, time to show Krad the power of the true warriors, "
"the warriors of Temsk!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:769
msgid ""
"The mercenary leader can recruit Pagans - berserk units who can also build "
"idols via a rightclick menu. However, the mercenary leader cannot recruit "
"Ogre Kingdom units. Unlike your main leader, the death of the mercenary "
"leader does not count as defeat."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:794
msgid "No"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:798
msgid ""
"Your loss. If you change your mind, we'll still be staying here for a while."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:873
msgid ""
"Hmph, the retreating villagers are back with reinforcements. Another "
"nuisance to deal with..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:907
msgid ""
"Look, there's boats with enemy reinforcements! We should try to stop them, "
"or we'll have to fight a lot more enemies..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=enemy_leader
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:959
msgid "The invaders have entered the citadel! Time for our last stand!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:975
msgid "And so the city falls..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:990
msgid "Take that!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:1001
msgid "Yes! The glory of conquest is mine!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/3_Siege.cfg:1012
msgid "Very well."
msgstr ""

