msgstr ""

#. [note]
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:600
msgid ""
"White enemies guard the temple, but will arrange and attack in waves every 4 "
"turns"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Kingdom_Cleric
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:612
msgid "Listen! Listen to the Word of Light..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:617
msgid "Villagers, overcome by their curiosity, started listening..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:621
msgid ""
"Well, well, well. It looks even more promising than I thought, they started "
"to listen."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:625
msgid "This will require some time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:629
msgid ""
"Yes. And there is a danger: they have a temple of their old faith nearby. We "
"can't let it be, its presense will make any sermon pointless."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:633
msgid "Can we just storm it and demolish afterwards?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Pan
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:637
msgid ""
"No, it's guarded well... But scouts report they gather their forces to "
"incite a revolt here and take this land back. We should stay here, protect "
"the villages while our clerics are preaching, and defeat the Krad soldiers "
"when they come for us. If we can fend them off several times, they will be "
"weakened enough and we'll storm the temple."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Brother
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:641
msgid "Time to preach!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:711
msgid ""
"Damn it, too many villagers are dead! Ruling barren ruins is not worth it..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:875
msgid "The first wave is coming!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:894
msgid "More enemy troops on the way!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:913
msgid ""
"The enemy is sending their best troops. Once we beat them, we can capture "
"the temple with ease!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:952
msgid ""
"Now we should have more time to convert the villagers without being bothered."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: scenarios/4_Time_to_Preach.cfg:961
msgid "Indeed."
msgstr ""

